### Planning and initiative docs (`docs/wip/planning/`)

| Trigger file | Docs / artifact to update | Section / area |
|:-------------|:----------------------------|:---------------|
| New `docs/wip/planning/NN-<slug>/` folder | `docs/wip/planning/README.md` | Initiative index table (next `NN` slot, title, link to folder) |
| `docs/wip/planning/**/master-roadmap.md` (material phase or dependency change) | Same initiative folder; optional `reference/` plan mirror | Phase dependency narrative, mermaid diagram, and phase-at-a-glance stay aligned with the **authoritative** Cursor plan; fix internal links |
| `docs/wip/planning/**/reference/*.md` (git-tracked plan mirror) | Initiative `master-roadmap.md` link section | When the mirror is collaboration SSOT, update pointer text if the Cursor plan filename or path changes |
| Execution changes `docs/references/hlk/compliance/*.csv` or `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/**` | `docs/USER_GUIDE.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Same as **HLK compliance changes** above when those trees actually change (wip roadmap drafts alone do not require USER_GUIDE edits) |

**Planning insight:** Multi-phase HLK work should keep **phase order** explicit in `master-roadmap.md` (e.g. charter and crosswalk before CSV tranche; CSV tranche before v3.0 SOPs that cite new `item_id`s; stack/mirrors after SOPs for primary flows where SOP-META order applies). Optional **git mirror** of a Cursor plan under the initiative folder gives **version history** on the plan body; see `.cursor/rules/akos-planning-traceability.mdc`.

### Human-facing index and guides

| Trigger | Docs to update | Section / area |
|:--------|:----------------|:--------------|
| New **narrative** onboarding or workflow topic (tutorial / explanation) | `docs/README.md` | Add or adjust a row in “Read by role” and/or “Where different kinds of doc live”; link the new `docs/guides/<name>.md` |
| New cross-repo term in **3+** first-class docs (ARCHITECTURE, USER_GUIDE, DEVELOPER_CHECKLIST, etc.) | `docs/GLOSSARY.md` | One-line definition + “see” link |
| Change to **what** `verify` / `release-gate` / `run-evals` *mean* in prose (not argv) | `docs/guides/understanding_verification.md` | Must stay consistent with `config/verification-profiles.json` (if conflict, **config wins**); adjust narrative only when behavior is unchanged or doc was wrong |
| `docs/guides/<new>.md` | `docs/README.md` | Add link under the right audience or “Quick links” |

## Always update

After any user-facing change on this branch:

1. **CHANGELOG.md** -- add or update an entry under `[Unreleased]` using imperative mood
2. **README.md** -- if capabilities, prerequisites, or repo structure changed
3. **CONTRIBUTING.md** -- if new test groups, dependencies, or dev workflows were added

## Verification

After updating docs, spot-check:

- Internal markdown links resolve to real files (`](../path)` and `](path)`)
- Tables are well-formed (header + separator + data rows)
- No stale version numbers, container images, or default values in prose
- ASCII/mermaid diagrams match current code structure (**mermaid:** no spaces in node IDs; avoid reserved words like `end` as node IDs)
- Test count in ARCHITECTURE.md matches actual `tests/` file count if referenced
- Initiative **`master-roadmap.md`**: phase dependency bullets and diagram match the authoritative plan; `docs/wip/planning/README.md` lists the initiative when a **new** folder is added
